{"lemma":"أَكَمَةٌ","slug":"أَكَمَةٌ","root":"#.ك.م","root_slug":"_-ك-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ك-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَكَمَةٌ","root":"كمه","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1033"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"someone who is blind since birth","examples":[{"text":"وَأُبْرِئُ الْأَكْمَهَ وَالْأَبْرَصَ وَأُحْيِي الْمَوْتَىٰ بِإِذْنِ اللَّهِ","english":"I will heal the blind and the leper and raise the dead to life—by Allah’s Will."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ك م ه (k m h)."},"ipa":["/ʔak.mah/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1033","headword_ar":"اَكَمَةٌ","root":"Akm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tal~N","text_ar":"تَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) [in an absolute sense, or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~","text_ar":"قُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (K,) or, as in the M, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a single collection of stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inferior to mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place that is more elevated than what is around it, and is rugged, not to the degree of being stone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an isolated mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabalN","text_ar":"جَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eminence like what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAbiyap","text_ar":"رَابِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of stones in one place, sometimes rugged and sometimes not rugged:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~N","text_ar":"قُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akmp","text_ar":"اكمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is higher and greater:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is higher than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~","text_ar":"قُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact and round, rising into the sky, abounding with stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamaAtN","text_ar":"اَكَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamN","text_ar":"اَكَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or this is rather a coll. gen. n. of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamapN","text_ar":"اَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.,] (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAmN","text_ar":"اـِكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamN","text_ar":"اَكَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukumN","text_ar":"اُكُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAmN","text_ar":"اـِكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kaAmN","text_ar":"ا=كَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.], (K,) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukumN","text_ar":"اُكُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kumN","text_ar":"ا=كُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is also a pl. of pauc.], (IJ, K,) or this is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamN","text_ar":"اَكَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) IHsh says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamN","text_ar":"اَكَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the only word like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamarN","text_ar":"ثَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in its series of pls.; for its sing. [or n. un.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamapN","text_ar":"اَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of this [or the coll. gen. n.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamN","text_ar":"اَكَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAmN","text_ar":"اـِكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukumN","text_ar":"اُكُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=kaAmN","text_ar":"ا=كَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the pl. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAmiymu","text_ar":"اَكَامِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAkiymu","text_ar":"اَوَاكِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?]. (MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmr","text_ar":"ثمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is said in a prov., used in ridiculing any one who has told of his committing some fault, not desiring to reveal it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jusotumuwniY wawaraA='a AlA^akamapi maA waraA='ahaA","text_ar":"جُسْتُمُونِى وَوَرَا=ءَ الاَكَمَةِ مَا وَرَا=ءَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which I think the first word to be a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otumuwniY","text_ar":"جِيْتُمُونِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the literal meaning to be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye have come to me; but behind the hill is what is behind it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: related on the authority of Zeyd Ibn-Kethweh. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tabulo EalaY","text_ar":"لَا تَبُلْ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akampK","text_ar":"اَكَمةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Publish not what is secret of thine affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","ISh","S","IJ"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}